cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a novel multi-agent reinforcement learning algorithm that generalizes over state space and different scenarios. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with multi-agent systems, which makes it relevant to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. The proposed algorithm is applied to a 2D environment, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the environment involves visual perception, which makes it relevant to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
